<br>
Just for the record, I've seen Amon in the spot the poster above mentioned, but have also found him in the pit, in the middle of the maze (that was a fun one to find-we ran around for 30 minutes killing things and using sense the dead), as well as in the NW corner of the maze and behind the door leading to the exit mirror.<br>
<br>
The reason I didn't recommend using the passage with the fake wall is just on the other side of that is the &quot;ambush point&quot; as we always called it-the place I mentioned where tons of mobs can agro you in a row-the rare see invis mob also seems to show up in this hallway alot. By taking the path I mentioned, you spend the absolute least amount of time in that ambush area and, if you have people with you who aren't used to the zone, the path is easier for them to follow you on and I personally prefer to spend the absolute least amount of time possible moving around on this floor-too many wandering mobs that can gang up to do an insane amount of damage quickly-those Force Shock spells add up FAST when you have three or four shadows chain-casting them on you.<br>
<br>
Overall, though, I love ToFS and still try to get back every so often to lead a run on Tserrina or just a general dungeon crawl for people who haven't been there before-its a fun place to explore-wish there were more zones like it in the game. Hats off to its designer. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#FF0000>- </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse>The Safehouse</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13>Quests of Norrath</a> <font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href="http://www.thesafehouse.org">The Safehouse website</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font> <center><a href="http://www.guildboss.com"><img
